## 11. SIMULATION ENGINE (Section 4.9)

### Purpose
Enable what-if scenario analysis with persistent storage and comparison capabilities.

### Responsibilities
- Create scenarios forked from baseline or other scenarios
- Apply event-sourced changes (deltas)
- Materialize scenarios (apply all deltas to get full state)
- Compare scenarios to each other or baseline
- Promote scenarios to become new baselines

### Interfaces
```typescript
interface Scenario {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  status: 'ACTIVE' | 'PROMOTED' | 'ARCHIVED';
  forkedFromBaselineId?: string;
  forkedFromScenarioId?: string;
  expiresAt: Date;  // Auto-expire after 30 days of inactivity
}

interface ScenarioDelta {
  scenarioId: string;
  sequenceNum: number;
  deltaType: 'PM_MOVE' | 'PM_ADD' | 'PM_REMOVE';
  entityType: string;
  entityId: string;
  oldValues: object;
  newValues: object;
  changeReason: string;
}
```

### Key Methods
- `createScenario()` - Fork from baseline or scenario
- `applyChange()` - Record event-sourced delta
- `materializeScenario()` - Build full state from base + deltas
- `compareScenarios()` - Calculate PM, manhour, cost differences
- `promoteToBaseline()` - Apply scenario to production and create baseline

### Dependencies
- BaselineService
- Database (scenarios, scenarioDeltas, scenarioComparisons tables)

