## Hard vs Soft Constraints

### Hard Constraints (NEVER violate)
1. Train fitness status (only FIT trains assigned)
2. Unavailability events block scheduling
3. Service demand minimum requirements
4. Route compatibility restrictions
5. Material availability within 14 days (blocking parts)
6. Compliance window boundaries

### Soft Constraints (Violate with penalty)
1. Mileage balance (prefer under-utilized trains)
2. Route preference
3. Material availability 15-90 days out (warning)
4. Track utilization target (85%)
5. Labor utilization target

